Open includes/GlobalFunctions.php. At approximately line 370, change the following:$forward = "\t(proxied via {$_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR']}{$forward})";to$forward = "\t(proxied via {$_SERVER['HTTP_CF_CONNECTING_IP']}{$forward})";
Open includes/ProxyTools.php. At approximately line 79, find:if ( isset( $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ) ){and replace with:if ( isset( $_SERVER['HTTP_CF_CONNECTING_IP'] ) ){The second step only applies to MediaWiki versions 1.18.0 and older. Newer versions of MediaWiki have completely rewritten ProxyTools.php and the following code is no longer present.
Find at approximately line 80:$ipchain = array( IP::canonicalize($_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR']) );Save and upload to your origin web server.

For versions around 1.27.1:

Go to line 1232 in GlobalFunctions.php, change REMOTE_ADDR to HTTP_CF_CONNECTING_IP.
Next, go to WebRequest.php, in lines 1151 to line 1159, change REMOTE_ADDR to HTTP_CF_CONNECTING_IP.

